<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-541-091  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 541 091.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  Oct 22 1990 v36 n1832 p32(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Senate appropriates $268.2B for DOD, freezes ATCCS CPUs. (billion)(Department of Defense, Army Tactical Command and Control System)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robertson, Jack.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>As part of its $268.2 billion FY 1991 military appropriationsbill, the US Senate froze all money for Army Tactical Command andControl Systems (ATCCS) software pending approval by a DefenseDepartment review board.andP;  The House passed a $269.1 millionmilitary appropriations bill.andP;  The Senate flatly rejected $768million requested for the Milstar defense communication satelliteand $144 million for General Electric's AN/BSY-2 combat controlsystem for the SSN-21 attack submarine.andP;  Funding for the WorldWide Military Command and Control System (WWMCCS) InformationSystem upgrade was frozen pending DOD approval.andP;  The Senate didauthorize $50 million more than requested for high-definitionresearch by the Defense Advance Research Projects Agency.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Congress. SenateUnited States. Department of DefenseDefense contractsWorldwide Military Command and Control System (Defense program).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>